{"parse":{"title":"Respectful workplace","pageid":42079498,"revid":794011871,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>respectful workplace</b> is a safe place of employment where employees are valued, recognised, treated fairly have clear expectations, and work harmoniously.<sup id=\"cite_ref-apsc4_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-apsc4-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Benefits\">Benefits</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Respectful_workplace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Benefits\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Benefits of a respectful workplace include better moral, teamwork, lower absenteeism, lower turnover of staff, reduced <a href=\"/wiki/Worker%27s_compensation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Worker&#39;s compensation\">worker's compensation</a> claims,\nbetter ability to handle change and recover from problems, work seems less onerous, and improved productivity.\nPositively viewed teams will retain and employ better staff.\n</p><p>Lack of respect and what is sometimes called \"incivility\"\u2014low level negative behaviours (such as rudeness, discourteousness, not acknowledging other staff)\u2014can create a dysfunctional team environment, relationship breakdown, decline in productivity, and the risk of psychological injury.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Process\">Process</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Respectful_workplace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Process\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Managers that want to encourage a respectful workplace must model the appropriate example.\nThey should talk about what behaviours are encouraged.\nThe managers must be willing to talk about problem behaviours.\nThere should be safe ways to report problems, which could be anonymous, or independent people such as an ombudsman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Measures of the culture could include competitiveness, formality, respect, hospitality and supportiveness.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Respect can be included in performance appraisals, with feedback given in a formal process. Disrespectful behaviour must not be ignored but be named and its impact brought to the attention of the responsible person. By ignoring problematic behaviour, others will perceive it as condoned.\n</p><p><br />\n</p><p>The Compassionate organisation will have strategies that deal with problems affecting the well being of employees such as redundancies, disasters, workplace conflict.  There would be strategies that recover from distress.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-frost_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-frost-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Respectful_workplace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-apsc4-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-apsc4_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.apsc.gov.au/publications-and-media/current-publications/mental-health/a-respectful-workplace\">\"-  4. Creating a respectful workplace\"</a>. <i>Promoting mental health and wellbeing at work</i>. Australian Public Service Commission<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 March</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Promoting+mental+health+and+wellbeing+at+work&amp;rft.atitle=-++4.+Creating+a+respectful+workplace&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.apsc.gov.au%2Fpublications-and-media%2Fcurrent-publications%2Fmental-health%2Fa-respectful-workplace&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARespectful+workplace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.unb.ca/towardarespectfulworkplace/safe.html\">\"TOWARDS A RESPECTFUL WORKPLACE\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 March</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=TOWARDS+A+RESPECTFUL+WORKPLACE&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww2.unb.ca%2Ftowardarespectfulworkplace%2Fsafe.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARespectful+workplace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.unb.ca/towardarespectfulworkplace/climate.html\">\"Assess workplace culture\"</a>. <i>TOWARDS A RESPECTFUL WORKPLACE</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 March</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=TOWARDS+A+RESPECTFU